dc_description_s: The Red River Basin Mapping Initiative 2008-2010 project acquired 1.4-meter Lidar data for the US portion of the Red River Basin. Additionally, imagery was collected for the main corridor of the basin. Information about the full initiative (IWI Red River Basin Mapping 2008-2010 - LiDAR) can be referenced at http://www.mngeo.state.mn.us/chouse/metadata/iwi_rrbmi_08_10_lidar.html This data set is the result of private and government entities working together under the guidance of the International Water Institute (IWI) regarding the Red River Basin Mapping Initiative (RRBMI). The United States Army Corps of Engineers (USACE) St Louis District was one of the major contributors in this funding effort.
dc_relation_sm: This imagery was collected in conjunction with a larger mapping initiative that incompassed 1.4-m LiDAR data acquisition. For more information see the International Water Institute Red River Basin Mapping Initiative 2008-2010 - LiDAR Acquisition web page: http://www.iwinst.org/lidar/ Metadata for the LiDAR project is at http://www.mngeo.state.mn.us/chouse/metadata/iwi_rrbmi_08_10_lidar.html.
